The Supreme Court on Wednesday affirmed the election of Okezie Ikpeazu as Abia Governor. The Supreme Court had scheduled judgment for 2pm in the Abia State governorship dispute between Okezie Ikpeazu of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) and Alex Otti of the All Progressive Grand Alliance (APGA). Breaking: Court to deliver judgment in Abia gov’norship dispute today A seven-man of the Supreme Court, led by Justice Olabode Rhodes-Vivour, after taking arguments from lawyers to parties delivered judgement today. Details shortly…